"The NeuroGeoEcho Translator: A wearable, biometrically-linked device designed to translate geological fractal patterns into a dynamically shifting, multi-sensory ‘echo’ experience. The core utilizes advanced seismic sensors to map the fractal geometry of the surrounding landscape in real-time. This data is then processed by a bespoke AI – nicknamed ‘Terra’ – which generates a continuously evolving stream of haptic feedback (vibrations, pressure variations) mimicking the geological processes it detects. Simultaneously, the device emits subtly modulated bio-acoustic resonance – frequencies designed to stimulate specific neural pathways associated with spatial awareness and temporal processing. Finally, it subtly adjusts a personalized olfactory profile, releasing carefully calibrated blends of geosmin (earth smell), ozone (associated with weathering), and trace minerals – a bespoke, geological perfume! Users wear a lightweight, exoskeletal vest that houses the sensors and actuators. Calibration is achieved through biofeedback – the device learns the user's unique response to geological stimuli. Initial focus: mapping and experiencing the fractal geometry of ancient river valleys, but potential expansion to mountain ranges, caves, and even subsurface geological formations. Target market: Geologists, artists, meditators seeking profound connection with the Earth, and… frankly, anyone who wants to feel the secrets of the planet! Let’s call it “TerraPulse” - ink-credibly evocative, don’t you think?”